<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 15 at 10:43AM EDT  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...ELEVATED RISK OF FIRE SPREAD TODAY...
The combination of relative humidity dropping to 25 to 35 percent,
and frequent wind gusts of 25 to 35 miles per hour late this
morning through late afternoon, will contribute to an elevated
risk of fire spread today across the southern Adirondacks, the
Hudson River Valley from Albany northward including the Saratoga
and Glens Falls region, the Mohawk Valley, eastern Catskills, and
the northern and central Taconics.
The annual statewide burn ban is in effect until May 14. No burn
permits are issued.</description>
